data.title: Christina Milian is stylishly casual as she cuddles up with husband Matt Pokora during family outing
data.meta_description: Christina Milian flashed a cheerful smile as she took a loving snap with her husband and French singer, Matt Pokora, during a fun family outing in a new Instagram photo series shared on Monday.
data.text:
Christina Milian dressed warmly in cargo sweatpants and flashed a loving smile as she cuddled up next to her husband, Matt Pokora, in a new Instagram photo series shared on Monday.

The Love Don't Cost A Thing actress, 41, additionally uploaded adorable snaps of her children, Violet Nash, 12, whom she shares with ex, The-Dream, along with Isaiah, 2, and one-year-old Kenna, whom she welcomed with the French singer, 37.

The talented performer, who recently appeared in the Starz series, Step Up, for three seasons, penned a short caption to her 7.2 million followers, 'Kicking it in Calabasas.'

The Dip It Low hitmaker bundled up as her family braved the rainy California weather over the long weekend, and donned a pair of olive-green, cargo-styled sweatpants.

The warm bottoms were tucked into a pair of fashionable, black belted boots to protect her feet from the numerous puddles scattered on the sidewalk.

Christina threw on a long-sleeved sweater that contained both olive-green and cream-colored hues with an adjustable zipper around the neck.

The mother of three added a matching purse outlined in black over her right shoulder to complete her overall ensemble for the chilly, daytime outing.

Christina's locks were slicked up into a stylish bun and a pair of black sunglasses were placed on top of her head in case the bright sunshine peaked through the gray clouds.

In the first snap, the actress embraced her husband, Matt, who also goes by the name of M. Pokora. The two lovebirds tied the knot in 2020, after the couple began officially dating three years earlier in 2017.

The French singer also opted for comfort, and threw on a plain, crew-neck gray sweatshirt, along with a black top underneath for an additional layer. He slipped into a pair of warm joggers and black and white-patterned sneakers that were secured tightly with laces.

Matt's arms were also lovingly wrapped around his wife's as they flashed happy smiles for the camera.

During a recent interview with BET Lifestyle, Christina explained how she and her husband enjoy traveling as often as possible with each other. 'We don't go too far away from the kids,' she stated, 'but we like to do something for ourselves. We need that time to just be adults and not have to worry about anything.'

She continued to the publication, 'Every time we do it, it is always really refreshing. I love to travel and I love spontaneity. Thank goodness he has that in him because it's a good fit for the both of us.'

In the second photo, the When You Look At Me singer and Matt posed with Christina's oldest child, Violet Nash. She shares her mini-me with The-Dream, whom she tied the knot with in 2009 at the Little White Chapel in Las Vegas.

However, later that same year, the two decided to separate, with their divorce being finalized in October 2011.

The last picture in the photo series showed her two sons, Isaiah and Kenna, looking over a railing at the flowing water below them. The siblings were also bundled up in colorful puffer vests and knit beanies to stay warm in the cooler temperatures.

When talking to Us Weekly, Christina opened up about her typical weekend, especially Sundays, expressing that, 'youd probably find me out with my husband and kids at a park or a family event.'

Aside from spending time with her loved ones and raising her children, Christina has also been working hard in the entertainment industry.

The talented star will be seen once again on the big screen in the upcoming thriller titled, Body Language, and has also taken on the role of producing the project.

'I am so excited to be producing my first film and starring in it as well,' the singer stated, according to Deadline. 'It is a thriller, something I havent done before.'

The beauty added, 'I really resonated with this story because it is absolutely something that can happen in real life which, to me, makes it even scarier.'

The movie has also cast The Expanse actor, Steven Strait, and follows Christina's character, Mariana, who, 'excels at reading people. But what happens when she lets her guard down during dinner with her fianc's enigmatic college friend, who seems to be one step ahead of her?' according to an IMDB synopsis.

With the project still in post-production stages, a set premiere date has yet to be revealed.
